1b:["$","article",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__articlePage","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"Modern Deck Railing Trends: Cable, Glass, and Composite\",\"image\":[\"https://www.ldndecks.com/images/img50.jpeg\"],\"datePublished\":\"2026-04-22T04:00:00.000Z\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-04-22T04:00:00.000Z\",\"author\":[{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Nick - Loudoun Decks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\"}],\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\",\"logo\":{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/ldndecks-logo.webp\"}},\"description\":\"Transitioning from wood pickets to sleek, low-obstruction railing systems. Discover how modern railings can transform your view and safety.\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/blog/modern-deck-railing-trends-2026\"},\"isAccessibleForFree\":true,\"inLanguage\":\"en-US\",\"speakable\":{\"@type\":\"SpeakableSpecification\",\"cssSelector\":[\".leadParagraph\",\"h1\",\"h2\"]}}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgWrapper","children":[["$","$L24",null,{"src":"/images/img50.jpeg","alt":"Modern Deck Railing Trends: Cable, Glass, and Composite","fill":true,"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroImg","priority":true,"sizes":"100vw"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgOverlay","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerLarge","children":[["$","$L18",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__backLink","children":"← Back to News"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__title","children":"Modern Deck Railing Trends: Cable, Glass, and Composite"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__meta","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__author","children":["By ","Nick - Loudoun Decks"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__divider","children":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"$undefined","children":"April 22, 2026"}]]}]]}]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerNarrow","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentBody","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__leadParagraph","children":"Transitioning from wood pickets to sleek, low-obstruction railing systems. Discover how modern railings can transform your view and safety."}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"In the past, the railing was often the most overlooked part of a deck—usually just 2x2 pressure-treated wood pickets that eventually warped and turned gray. In 2026, the railing is a primary design element. Homeowners are demanding systems that are both highly durable and virtually invisible."}],["$","h2","1",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"Horizontal Cable Railing: The Modern Standard"}],["$","p","2",{"children":"Cable railing has exploded in popularity across Fairfax and Loudoun County. Using marine-grade stainless steel cables spaced exactly 3 inches apart, this system offers an industrial-chic look that is incredibly strong. More importantly, because the cables are so thin, they do not block your view of the garden or woods beyond. It is the perfect choice for properties with beautiful landscape views."}],["$","h2","3",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"Tempered Glass: For the Ultimate Panorama"}],"$L25","$L26","$L27"],"$L28"]}]}]}],"$L29"]}]
25:["$","p","4",{"children":"For homeowners with waterfront properties or truly breathtaking views, glass railing panels are the gold standard. Utilizing 3/8-inch tempered safety glass held by aluminum clips, this system provides 100% visibility while acting as an effective windbreak. While it requires occasional cleaning to remove smudges, the architectural impact is unmatched for modern, high-end homes."}]
26:["$","h2","5",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"Composite and Aluminum Hybrid Systems"}]
27:["$","p","6",{"children":"If you prefer a more traditional look but want zero maintenance, hybrid systems combine the \"bulk\" of a composite post with the sleekness of aluminum balusters. These systems are incredibly rigid and won’t rattle in the wind. We often match the post color to the picture-frame border of the deck flooring for a cohesive, designer-curated look."}]
